Mobilizing young patients: AFM Telethon wants to enable its young people to take action and participate in the leadership of the association created and governed initially by and for patients and their families.

9 students from Télécom SudParis wish to join this mobilization through 2 main objectives:

  • To help young patients to carry out their integrated projects within the AFM's youth project incubator (15-25 years old) by sharing their recent skills in project management (feasibility, financing, communication...)
  • Co-organize the large annual national meeting planned for spring 2020 by proposing workshops and/or conferences chosen by patients and their families and by promoting the incubator of young AFM projects.

) }
